  "body": "We are using react with cordova to build a hybrid mobile application. All the images are rendering on inspect browser but not on the actual device.\r\n\r\nWe have tried the following approach to render image -\r\n\r\n1.\r\nimport redcar from './RedCar.png'\r\n`<image src={redcar} />`\r\n2.\r\nvar redcar = require('./RedCar.png')\r\n`<image src={redcar} />`\r\n3.\r\n`<img src=\"./RedCar.png\" />\r\n`4.\r\nCopied image into android\\assets folder and tried\r\n`<image src='/android_asset/www/RedCar.png' responsive />`\r\n5.\r\nindex.html\r\n`<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Security-Policy\" content=\"default-src *; style-src * 'unsafe-inline'; script-src * 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; media-src *; img-src * filesystem: data:\">`\r\n\r\n6. Only way it's rendering the image son device is by giving a background image to <div> in css file.\r\nBut we need to read the image paths from JSON so we can't use this approach.\r\nbackground-image: url(\"./RedCar.png\");\r\n\r\n7. \r\nAlso I tried changing the webpack output->publicpath to \"\\\" or \"assets\" and making use of url-loader / file-loader but couldn't get it right .\r\n\r\nThe images are supposed to render on device.\r\n\r\nReact version - 15.3.1 \r\n",
